    "As the twilight shimmers on the waters of the Chao Phraya River, our journey leads us back onto the streets of Bangkok, where the Ananta Samakhom Throne Hall awaits. Completed in nineteen fifteen during the reign of King Chulalongkorn, or Rama the Fifth, the Throne Hall narrates stories of royal ceremonies within its stunning, Italian Renaissance and Neo Classic walls." /
